SUMMARY:Matcha Mahjong Mixer🍵
LOCATION:New York\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nDear founders and investors\,\n\nIf you made it
  this far\, you're invited to the next Matcha Mahjong Mixer — brought to
  you by Leo AI and Reitler.\n\nThis is an evening for the people actually 
 building it. The ones shipping in the middle of an industry that reshuffle
 s itself with every new Claude and OpenAI release\, who made the hard call
 s\, carried the early risk\, and know what it means to go from zero to som
 ething real.\n\nWe're creating a highly social environment where conversat
 ions and connections actually flow — far from the typical "future of wor
 k" panel. No decks\, no pitches\, no name-tag-and-business-card grind. Jus
 t a small room of sharp people and good conversation.\n\nHere's the twist:
  we play mahjong. Four seats to a table\, tiles in hand\, matcha in your c
 up. It sounds unusual\, and that's the point — nothing breaks the ice an
 d gets strangers talking like sitting down to learn a game together. No ex
 perience needed. We'll teach you in ten minutes\, and you'll be trash-talk
 ing your table by the second round.\n\nThe setting is intimate: a private 
 members' club in Midtown\, dim and unhurried\, with a matcha courtesy of R
 eitler. Think founders across AI\, SaaS\, fintech\, consumer\, and everyth
 ing in between — alongside the seed-to-Series-A investors who back them.
  People who've been in the trenches and have something worth saying.\n\nOu
 r goal is simple: we want you to leave with at least 3 high-value connecti
 ons — the kind you'll actually use.\n\nAbout the organizers\n\nLeo AI us
 es social signals to help marketing teams launch new channels by turning h
 ours of unused content into data-driven video storytelling. Finalist at th
 e 2025 Startup Awards and one of the UK's top 10 AdTech startups. Leo AI e
 mpowers companies to focus on what matters most: telling their story to th
 e audience most likely to become their customers.\n\nReitler Kailas & Rose
 nblatt LLP is a New York-based full service boutique law firm that deliver
 s responsive\, high quality legal services to sophisticated business clien
 ts. Reitler possesses leading capabilities in venture capital and private 
 equity financing's\, fund formation\, mergers and acquisitions\, securitie
 s offerings and capital markets\, real estate and hospitality\, as well as
  maritime and commercial litigation.\n\nResident Company Club is a curated
  workspace for startups\, founders\, and VCs\, designed to foster meaningf
 ul connections and collaboration. Coworking promised community\, but deliv
 ered strangers sharing Wi-Fi. Resident is a company club\, where every mem
 ber is intentionally selected for cultural fit and collective ambition. Le
 arn more here.\n\nWanna join? Spots are limited and the guest list is cura
 ted to keep the founder-to-investor balance right. Secure yours below and 
 make sure your perspective is part of the room.\n\nWe can't wait to see yo
 u there. 🍵🀄\n\nCalendar: Personal\n\nHosts: Lera Leonteva\, Theophil
 a Lee\, Jessica Casale\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/02uq48nz
URL:https://luma.com/02uq48nz
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
