SUMMARY:Field Notes Session No. 5 in collaboration with Fabrik
LOCATION:Fabrik NYC\, New York\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nEvery Field Note starts with one question: when
  do you feel most yourself?\n\nThe answer changes everything. People stop 
 describing their jobs and start describing their actual lives.\n\nField No
 tes Sessions brings that same question into a room. We'll write\, move\, a
 nd sit with images — yours and mine. You'll look underneath a moment in 
 your own life\, name something you've been doing anyway\, and read a stran
 ger's story and find something true in it.\n\nAt the end\, I'll share five
  patterns that have surfaced across fifty Field Notes — across every age
 \, industry\, and kind of life. Odds are good the room will have just live
 d every single one.\n\nPlease bring a photo with you of where you feel mos
 t yourself.\n\nCome be part of the record.\n\nP.S This Field Notes Session
  is in collaboration with Fabrik and will be hosted in the main space whic
 h means we will have more space! Please feel free to invite a pal\, collea
 gue or someone you think would enjoy this experience!\n\nAbout Fabrik\n\nF
 abrik is a home for communities where everyone has a place to belong. With
  spaces designed to feel more like your living room than your office\, Fab
 rik’s social spaces are vibrant hubs where people can come together in r
 eal life\, explore interests\, forge meaningful connections\, and build a 
 sense of community.\n\n*This event will be photographed and filmed. Fabrik
  reserves the right to use photos and video from the event for marketing a
 nd communications purposes. By attending the event\, you consent to the us
 e of your image for these purposes.\n\n*By RSVPing\, you agree to receive 
 communications from Fabrik related to this gathering and future offerings.
  You may unsubscribe anytime.\n\nAbout Subra Coffee\n\nSubra is a South In
 dian filter coffee brand reintroducing the bold\, smooth tradition of chic
 ory-blended filter coffee through tastings\, pop-ups\, and community gathe
 rings. Rooted in heritage and inspired by the idea that this coffee tradit
 ion deserves a more everyday place in the world\, Subra is all about makin
 g people feel at home in it.\n\nCalendar: Fabrik NYC\n\nHosts: Lindsey Ler
 ner\, Fabrik NYC\n\nVenue: Fabrik NYC\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/mhb9
 vvki
URL:https://luma.com/mhb9vvki
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
