SUMMARY:Touching Grass Tour 🌱 (Cadman Park Plaza)
LOCATION:Cadman Plaza Park\, Brooklyn\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nTouching Grass Tour \nWe started Yoga Club as a
  way to move\, unplug\, and actually meet people. Join us for our summer s
 eries in partnership with the NYC Parks Dept!\n\n☀️ Flowing vinyasa pr
 actice in the great outdoors\n🌊 Style: All-levels flow (accessible + re
 freshing)\n🙏 No yoga experience needed! Ideal for beginners and experie
 nced yogis. We mean it!!\n\nPlease RSVP fast\, we are limited in the numbe
 r of spots we can accommodate.\n\n📣 How to Sign Up \nPlease RSVP for fr
 ee here on Luma and present your ticket at the event.\n\nBYOM (Bring Your 
 Own Mat)\n\n📍 Where & When \nCadman Park Plaza (Look for the yellow Yog
 a Club flag!)\n\nGathering starts at 6:00pm. Practice begins once the spac
 e fills\,  about 15–20 minutes after\, and runs for an hour. Schmooze to
  follow.\n\n🌿 What to Expect \nWe're a club\, not a class. Come as you 
 are\, say hello to the people around you\, and settle in.\n\nOur Vinyasa p
 ractices are for all levels and run about an hour. Expect to move and brea
 the through an energizing set of standing postures and rejuvenating poses 
 on the ground.\n\nWe understand that life happens. Sometimes that means sh
 owing up late\, in your PJs\, or both. We leave some time at the beginning
  of our meetings to ease in and socialize.\n\nAfter Yoga \nStick around. S
 ocializing afterwards.\n\n📵 Your Phone\nTouching Grass means stepping a
 way from digital distractions.\n\nWe ask that you don't use your phone dur
 ing the gathering. We don't take phones away. You can use yours for emerge
 ncies or step away from the group if you need to. We just ask everyone to 
 follow the honor system.\n\nIt helps people slow down and stay present.\n\
 n⭐ Our Instructor \nDan Sohval came to yoga seeking ways to build inner 
 discipline and mental balance. He is the founder of Yoga Club. A lifelong 
 educator\, he brings to his instruction the same humor and curiosity that 
 guides his teaching in the classroom. He received his 200-hour certificati
 on at VeraYoga with additional training in yin and trauma-informed practic
 es. Off the mat\, he is a published author\, teaches computer science\, an
 d is an avid fan of Korean food.\n\n💫 About Yoga Club \nWe bring people
  together through high quality\, affordable yoga and community. We meet in
  creative spaces around the city to move\, breathe\, and meet new people.\
 n\nCalendar: New York Yoga Club\n\nHosts: NY Yoga Club\n\nVenue: Cadman Pl
 aza Park\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/Touching-Grass-Cadman
URL:https://luma.com/Touching-Grass-Cadman
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
