SUMMARY:(N)YC Alumni + Founder Friends Monthly #19 by Rho and NYC Founders 
 Club
LOCATION:New York\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nJoin YC Alumni and friends for our recurring ca
 sual meetup. This gathering is designed to bring together ambitious\, fund
 ed founders of fast-growing companies for an evening of high-level network
 ing and community building.\n\nThe NYC Founders Club was established by YC
  Alumni (Aakash Shah\, Adam Alpert\, and Mike Wang) to foster a tight-knit
  ecosystem for builders. Whether you're looking to share insights or conne
 ct with peers\, we’d love to see you there.\n\nOur Partner\n\nSponsored 
 by Rho 🏦✨ the all-in-one financial platform built for startups. From 
 high-yield savings to integrated spend management\, Rho helps high-growth 
 teams stay lean and move fast.\n\nBy registering\, you consent to receivin
 g communications from NYC Founders Club regarding this event and future op
 portunities. By participating in this Rho-sponsored event\, you acknowledg
 e that you may be photographed or recorded. You grant irrevocable consent 
 to Rho and its partners to use your likeness in promotional materials with
 out compensation. You consent to receive marketing communications and news
 letters from Rho. You may unsubscribe at any time.\n\nRho is a fintech com
 pany\, not a bank. Checking and card services provided by Webster Bank\, N
 .A.\, member FDIC\; savings account services provided by American Deposit 
 Management\, LLC\, and its partner banks.\n\nCalendar: NYC Founders Club\n
 \nHosts: Aakash Shah (NYC Founders Club)\, Jordan Deasy\, Drew Parten\, Re
 mi Chester\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/xi9scrwx
URL:https://luma.com/xi9scrwx
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
