SUMMARY:WHOOPS - Interactive Art Pop-Up by ARTIACT
LOCATION:24-20 Jackson Ave\, Queens\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nWe've been waiting to do this one! WHOOPS is AR
 TIACT's first Activation Pop-up\, four days of art you can't just stand an
 d look at.\n\nEvery work in the show is interactive\, which means none of 
 it finishes itself. It waits for you to touch it\, move through it\, or fi
 gure out how to talk to it. We brought six artists together because their 
 work shares a refusal: it will not be looked at from a polite distance. So
  we built the show around what each piece needs\, and we're asking you to 
 do the same thing the work does\, which is pay attention with your hands.\
 n\nYou'll see work by Lu Lyu\, Han Bao\, Miguel Gallego\, Julia Daser\, Mi
 nami Matsumoto\, and Jackie Nam.\n\nFour days\, four nights\, each one its
  own thing. Thursday opens the show. Friday through Sunday\, we run daytim
 e hours\, 12 to 8 PM\, with a different evening program every night\, buil
 ding to the loudest closing we can pull off.\n\nFree to walk in and tune i
 n for the evening programs.\n\nDress Code🫪: Anything that makes people 
 go WHOOPS.\n\nshow up. touch something. stay.\n\nActivated by ARTIACT\nAct
 ivators: Alicia Zhang and Yasmine Wei\n@artiact.art\n\nCalendar: Personal\
 n\nHosts: ARTIACT\n\nVenue: 24-20 Jackson Ave\n\nEvent page: https://luma.
 com/jpvvsuo3
URL:https://luma.com/jpvvsuo3
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
