SUMMARY:"I Wait" Music Video Premiere with Ali Sethi
LOCATION:New Museum\, New York\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nPremiere Screening of "I Wait" by Ali Sethi fol
 lowed by a moderated discussion with artist Ali Sethi and director Haya Wa
 seem\, moderated by Puja Patel\, former Editor in Chief of Pitchfork.\n\nD
 oors open at 6:30pm. Screening begins promptly at 7pm.\n\nKindly note a co
 nfirmed RSVP does not guarantee admission. Seating is available on a first
 -come\, first-served basis\, and we encourage guests to arrive early.\n\n-
 --\n\nAli Sethi is a Pakistani-American singer\, composer and storyteller 
 whose music advances a syncretic South Asian identity. Fusing classical ra
 gas with contemporary beats\, his music feels “stealthily subversive” 
 (The New Yorker) and marries the metaphors of Punjabi poetry with camp and
  queer sensibilities. In 2022\, his song Pasoori became the first Pakistan
 i single to top Spotify's Global Viral Chart\, and was Google's most 'hum-
 to-search' song in the world. In 2022\, he was named to Time's '100 Next' 
 list\, his music praised for showing that “differences of culture\, lang
 uage\, religion and gender do not need to be antagonistic\; they can\, and
  always have\, enriched us\, and given us some of our greatest works of ar
 t.”\n\nHaya Waseem is a Pakistani-born\, Canadian filmmaker. Raised in S
 witzerland and based in Brooklyn\, she is multilingual with a documentary 
 editing background. Her debut feature\, Quickening\, premiered to critical
  acclaim at the Toronto International Film Festival. Her Work/Life campaig
 n for Publicis Groupe won the Grand Prix for Good at Cannes Lions. Haya is
  an alumna of the Canadian Film Centre Director Lab and TIFF Filmmaker Lab
 . Haya brings her eclectic upbringing and craft driven approach\, often sh
 ooting on 35mm and 65mm\, to every project.\n\nAbout Object & Animal\nObje
 ct & Animal is a film production company spanning across music\, advertisi
 ng\, documentary\, and narrative. Our work has been recognized by the indu
 stry's leading awards\,  including Cannes Lions\, D&AD\, British Arrows\, 
 Ciclope\, and APA. In 2019\, 2024\, and 2025 we were named UKMVA Productio
 n Company of the Year.  We have produced work across genres for artists in
 cluding Charli xcx\, Billie Eilish\, Harry Styles\, Andre 3000\, KATSEYE\,
  Chappell Roan\, Taylor Swift\, Geese\, and FKA Twigs\, amassing billions 
 of views. Our music videos have earned numerous MTV Video Music Awards and
  three Grammy nominations.\n\nAbout NEW INC\nExpanding on the New Museum
 ’s commitment to new art and new ideas\, NEW INC is the Museum’s cultu
 ral incubator supporting creative practitioners and small businesses worki
 ng across art\, design\, and technology. Now in Year 12\, NEW INC’s memb
 ership model continues to support a diverse range of creative practitioner
 s with a values-driven program and safe space for gathering and developing
  new creative projects and businesses. In 2020\, NEW INC launched ONX Stud
 io\, an XR accelerator for artists\, in partnership with the Onassis Found
 ation. NEW INC was cofounded by New Museum’s Toby Devan Lewis Director L
 isa Phillips and former Deputy Director Karen Wong in 2014 as the first mu
 seum-led cultural incubator.\n\nCalendar: Personal\n\nHosts: Object & Anim
 al\, NEW INC\n\nVenue: New Museum\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/edixqcls
URL:https://luma.com/edixqcls
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
