SUMMARY:NYC Pizza Crawl #16 - Long Island City
LOCATION:Queens\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nSince the first Saturday of July falls on July 
 4th\, i'm going to move the pizza crawl so everyone can enjoy the weekend.
 \n\nEvent Details\n\nDate: Saturday\, July 11\, 2026.\n\nMeeting Location:
  TBD\n\nMeeting Time: 12:00PM\n\nLength of crawl: About 3 hours.\n\nCost: 
 Pay as you go. You are paying for your own pizza so you can eat as much as
  your heart desires!\n\nWant to keep up with all our pizza adventures? Fol
 low along on Instagram 👉 https://www.instagram.com/newyorkcitypizzacraw
 l/\n\nWhat is ‘NYC Pizza Crawl?\n\nWe’re bringing people together from
  all backgrounds through a shared love of pizza. Each month\, we explore a
  different NYC neighborhood\, sampling slices from four standout pizza sho
 ps. But this isn’t just about the food—it’s about connection\, conve
 rsation\, and community.\n\nWhat sets our crawls apart is the focus on bui
 lding new friendships along the way. As you savor some of the city’s bes
 t slices\, you’ll have plenty of opportunities to engage in great conver
 sations and get to know your fellow pizza adventurers. After all\, the hea
 rt of this group isn’t just pizza—it’s the people who come together 
 to enjoy it.\n\nRules for Attendees\n\nBy attending a NYC Pizza Crawl even
 t\, you agree to the following:\n\nBe Kind & Respectful to others\n\nLet
 ’s keep the good vibes going by being kind—to each other and to those 
 around us. We’re here for great pizza and even better company\, so let
 ’s make sure everyone feels welcome and respected.\n\nIf you ever feel u
 ncomfortable or notice someone acting inappropriately\, please let me or a
  team member know right away. We have a zero-tolerance policy for bad beha
 vior—anyone who violates this may be asked to leave and will not be welc
 ome at future events. There is no three strike policy. One strike and you 
 are out.\n\nKindness and respect are the foundation of this community. Let
 ’s keep it that way.\n\nOpen to All\n\nWhether you're a local NYC reside
 nt\, a visitor from another state\, or traveling from overseas\, we warmly
  invite you to join our pizza crawls.\n\nSocial Atmosphere\n\nOur events a
 re naturally social and interactive. Please come prepared to engage with f
 ellow pizza enthusiasts and enjoy lively conversations.\n\nAllergy Awarene
 ss\n\nIf you have food allergies or gluten sensitivities\, please exercise
  caution when eating. Many pizza restaurants may have cross-contamination 
 in their kitchens\, so stay vigilant.\n\nEvent RSVPs\n\nTo maintain the qu
 ality of our events\, each one will have a limited number of spots. This e
 nsures that everyone has a great experience without overcrowding and long 
 wait times.\n\nWhen you RSVP to an event\, you’re committing to attend. 
 We understand that sometimes plans change\, so if you are unable to attend
 \, please change your RSVP.\n\nYour commitment helps us build a vibrant an
 d active community. To be fair to others\, repeated (2 strikes) no-shows i
 n a row will result in being banned from future events.\n\nEvent Photos/Vi
 deo\n\nBy participating in our events\, you consent to being photographed 
 or filmed. These photos and videos may be used for promotional and marketi
 ng purposes on Reddit and our website.\n\nDisclaimer\n\nOur events are ind
 ependently organized and not affiliated with Reddit Inc. This group is vol
 unteer-run with the goal of promoting the pizza community. We have no offi
 cial connection to Reddit Inc.\n\nCalendar: New York City Pizza Crawl\n\nH
 osts: Andrew Young\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/tckpoulp
URL:https://luma.com/tckpoulp
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
