DTSTAMP:20260706T020844Z
DTSTART:20260713T223000Z
DTEND:20260714T010000Z
SUMMARY:The Libi Journal Launch Party & 3rd Birthday Celebration :)
LOCATION:Hudson Wilder\, Brooklyn\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nJoin The Libi Project to celebrate the launch o
 f The Libi Journal @thelibjournal and to celebrate our 3rd birthday!\n\nAn
  extension of The Libi Project community\, The Libi Journal documents the
  stories of mission-driven individuals working at the intersection of food
 \, culture\, and entrepreneurship — the very people who have built the L
 ibi community over the past two years.\n\nPre-order your copy here!\n\nThe
  Libi Journal features:\n\nJess Eng @goudatalks\nBehzad Jamshidi @behzj\nT
 hu Pham Buser @thubuser\nCarlaFinley @apt2bread\nKiyomi Tanigawa @brooklyn
 _misomaru\n\nTo celebrate\, we'll have some delicious bites for purchase b
 y Chef Mei Liao x Day With Mei\, wine from Hudson Wilder\, and small-batch
  artisanal ice cream from Little Rat Ice Cream\, along with complimentary 
 drinks by NON\, a chef-crafted range of non-alcoholic beverages.\n\nMeijie
  “Mei” Liao @daywithmei is a James Beard Foundation and IACP–nominat
 ed recipe developer and content creator based in Brooklyn\, New York. Born
  to Sichuanese parents and raised in California\, she is the creator of @d
 aywithmei\, where she shares approachable recipes that work to dispel food
  stigmas. Her latest work explores the everyday rituals and values of the 
 Sichuanese diaspora\, from stewarding century-old pickles to championing o
 ffal.\n\nCharles & Susan Raben started Little Rat Ice Cream @littlerat.ice
 cream in the summer of 2025\, out of their kitchen in Ridgewood\, Queens. 
 Little Rat is a small-batch artisanal ice cream brand.\n\nNON is a chef-le
 d\, non-alcoholic beverage company redefining the drinking experience with
  bold\, uncompromising flavour. Born out of the fine dining scene and craf
 ted in Melbourne\, Australia\, NON creates wine alternatives that are made
  from real produce\, infused with culinary thinking\, and built to pair wi
 th food. They don’t mimic wine—NON makes something entirely new. Each 
 NON variant is carefully formulated with ingredients like whole fruits\, h
 erbs\, spices\, teas\, and verjus to deliver a complex\, layered drinking 
 experience without alcohol\, preservatives\, or artificial flavours.\n\nCa
 lendar: Personal\n\nHosts: The Libi Project\n\nVenue: Hudson Wilder\n\nEve
 nt page: https://luma.com/swm9m7p6
URL:https://luma.com/swm9m7p6
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-FJ1YhKVqvvrBvxr@luma.com
DTSTAMP:20260706T020844Z
DTSTART:20260714T220000Z
DTEND:20260715T010000Z
SUMMARY:Demo Night: Internal Design Tools
LOCATION:New York\, New York
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nThe way a design team works is shaped by the to
 ols they create\, from tiny scripts to full-fledged internal apps. Ramp an
 d South Park Commons are bringing together designers for an evening of lig
 htning talks highlighting internal design tools built for real teams.\n\nT
 he talks feature\n\nAmber Stickel\, Ramp\n\nRyan Mather\, Anthropic\n\nEdg
 ar Sze\, Profound\n\nFred Zaw\, Clay\n\nThe agenda\n\n6pm: Eat\, drink\, m
 ingle\n\n7:00pm: Talks begin\n\n8:00pm: More mingling\n\nThis event is in 
 NYC.\n\nSouth Park Commons is a technical community and venture fund dedic
 ated to helping founders\, researchers\, and technologists figure out what
  to work on next—what we call the -1 to 0 stage of your career. We belie
 ve this is best accomplished in the most talent-dense community possible. 
 If this is you\, apply for SPC membership.\n\nRamp is also hiring product 
 designers and design engineers. If you're thinking about what's next\, che
 ck out Ramp's careers page.\n\nCalendar: South Park Commons\n\nHosts: Sout
 h Park Commons\, Dylan Itzikowitz\, Elizabeth Lin\n\nEvent page: https://l
 uma.com/design-tool-demos
URL:https://luma.com/design-tool-demos
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
