UID:evt-bvdStxeXPiRB64y@luma.com
DTSTAMP:20260706T020844Z
DTSTART:20260714T230000Z
DTEND:20260715T010000Z
SUMMARY:Somartica
LOCATION:Reforesters Laboratory\, Kings County\, New York
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nSomartica:\nWhere movement meets creativity\n& 
 Presence meets play \n\nJoin us for a joyous evening where meditation mel
 ts into movement\, movement makes way to art\, and before you know it\, yo
 u're drawing on the walls\, rolling on the ground belly laughing\, and con
 necting with yourself and others in ways you forgot you remembered. 🤸
 🏽‍♀️\n\nSomartica blends somatics with art through research-backe
 d methods that help quiet your mind\, settle your nervous system\, and get
  you into flow. Doooope!\n\nThink of it like a one night summer camp. Or a
  nervous system reset. Or an art class. Or actually: all three.\n\nThe eve
 ning includes:\n✨ A somatic meditation ~ to help settle your nervous sys
 tem\n🌀 Intuitive movement  ~ to open into presence + flow\n🎨 Creativ
 e expression ~ with all manner of materials (Crayons! Paint! Yarn! Etc!)\n
 🤸🏽‍♀️ Pure\, unscripted play ~ to wiggle\, release\, giggle\n
 🌿 A closing circle ~ to leave refreshed + ready to re-enter the world\n
 \nYou'll laugh. You'll connect. You'll throw some paint around. And you mi
 ght even leave more grounded and more free.\n\nWhat people are saying:\n"S
 omartica is a blast."\n"I was out of my head and in a silly flow state the
  whole time!"\n\nNo experience necessary. Whether you're a seasoned artist
  and mover or total beginner\, you are welcome.\n\nCan't wait to see you!\
 n\nWear clothes you can move in.\n\nLed By: Nasimeh Be\, MA\n\nNasimeh Be\
 , MA\, is a coach\, facilitator\, artist\, and founder of Somartica – a 
 methodology and event series blending creativity\, embodiment\, and play. 
 With over a decade of experience creating transformative experiences for p
 eople of all ages\, her work has been featured at the Walt Disney Concert 
 Hall\, on Buzzfeed\, and on the Disney Channel. She holds a Master’s in 
 Psychology from Columbia University\, where her research focused on the in
 tersection of creativity\, embodiment\, and play. Find out more about her 
 - @nasimehbe\n\n***\n\nCome Early to Elevate Your Experience with Adaptoge
 nic Foods and Teas\n\nReforesters Laboratory is an experimental adaptogeni
 c cafe and sound clinic located in Williamsburg\, Brooklyn. We utilize mus
 ic – including spatial\, sub-bass-centered\, and organic instrumentation
  – along with breathwork\, meditation\, art\, plant care and adaptogenic
 \, nutritional foods + beverages to cultivate kindness—both physical and
  spiritual. We aim to create an environment that offers peace\, space\, an
 d clarity\, helping people understand the connections between themselves\,
  their communities\, and the world around them. To that end\, we offer aff
 ordable "pay what you can" ticket options on all events and classes.\n\nCa
 lendar: Reforesters Classes & Events\n\nHosts: Reforesters Laboratory\, Na
 simeh Be\n\nVenue: Reforesters Laboratory\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/
 vuoth4f3
URL:https://luma.com/vuoth4f3
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
