SUMMARY:HIGH RECEIPTS SCREENING - NEW YORK
LOCATION:Anthology Film Archives\, New York\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nHigh Receipts (38')\, a lyrical portrait of you
 th\, friendship\, and a Tokyo summer\, Directed by Matthew Ballard.\n\nSet
  in the endless heat of Tokyo\, four teenage friends (Yasu Chiba\, Soma Fu
 jita\, Kaito Nakajima\, Nobu Nori) play kendama\, chase small adventures\,
  and inhabit the freedom of youth. As the days unfold\, dreams and new way
 s of seeing the world begin to emerge.\n\n​Both intimate and atmospheric
 \, High Receipts is a poetic meditation on adolescence.\n\n​The screenin
 g will be followed by a Q&A with the director after the film.\n\nDoors ope
 n 7:30\n\nScreening begins 8:00\n\nCalendar: Personal\n\nHosts: matthew ba
 llard\n\nVenue: Anthology Film Archives\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/rp
 dd4h61
URL:https://luma.com/rpdd4h61
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
