UID:evt-7ld9WKrlEjLrM0Y@luma.com
DTSTAMP:20260706T020844Z
DTSTART:20260715T220000Z
DTEND:20260716T000000Z
SUMMARY:Writing the City with Diana Budds
LOCATION:Van Alen Institute\, Brooklyn\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nJoin journalist and design critic Diana Budds i
 n a summer workshop on reading\, and writing\, about the city we love.\n\n
 Budds will walk us through a curated selection of essays\, articles\, and 
 writings\, and then a group writing workshop will explore the themes of mi
 ssing stories and voices in our understanding of the city today.\n\nAttend
 ees will learn how to look more closely at the cityscape\, frame distinct 
 perspectives on place and space\, and share impactful narratives. The sess
 ion is grounded in the urban context of Gowanus\, a neighborhood that has 
 witnessed tremendous physical and cultural change in recent years\, and wi
 ll include a brief walking tour.\n\nThis workshop will culminate in a zine
  of collected writings by the group. All ages and levels of writing experi
 ence are welcomed and encouraged.\n\n6 pm — Doors open\, reading session
  beings\n6:30 pm — Group discussion and reflection\, led and guided by 
 Diana Budds\n7 pm — Personal writing time by the Gowanus Canal\n7:45 pm 
 — Regroup at Van Alen\; option to share work aloud\n\nThis event is pres
 ented by the Van Alen Vanguard\, a dynamic network of emerging design lead
 ers. Diana Budds is among the inaugural cohort developing public programs 
 and exhibitions that reimagine designers’ roles in civic life and center
  equity\, resilience\, and local knowledge.\n\nNotice of Access\, Filming\
 , and Photography\n\nVan Alen is committed to ensuring that all of our eve
 nts are inclusive and accessible for all participants. Van Alen Institute 
 is on the ground floor and ADA-accessible. If you require accommodations o
 r have any questions about access needs\, please email vai@vanalen.org and
  we will do our best to support your participation.\n\nWhen you attend thi
 s event\, you enter an area where photography\, audio\, and video recordin
 g may occur. By entering the event premises\, you consent to such recordin
 g media and its release\, publication\, exhibition\, or reproduction.\n\nC
 alendar: Van Alen Vanguard\n\nHosts: Van Alen Institute\, Diana Budds\n\nV
 enue: Van Alen Institute\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/g77pphge
URL:https://luma.com/g77pphge
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
