SUMMARY:A Chief of Staff Mixer on scaling (Thurs July 16)
LOCATION:New York\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nHi\, I am David Nebinski. I am the host of A Ch
 ief of Staff podcast and host events for Chiefs of Staff in New York.\n\nA
 re you looking to connect with other CoS in NYC about scaling?\n\nJoin thi
 s A Chief of Staff Mixer cohosted by me\, and Sheena Gohil and Jen Flores 
 from Colliers\n\nWhen: Thursday July 16th at 6:30 in Flatiron\n\nAgenda:\n
 \n6:30 - arrival and mingling\n\n7:00 - two mini chats on scaling\n\n7:30 
 - small group discussion on scaling\n\n8:00 - mingling\n\n📝 RSVP: This 
 event has limited capacity - so please RSVP as soon as you can.\n\n​​
 ​​​​​​​Excited to see you on Thursday July 16th\,​​\n\nD
 avid Nebinski who hosts monthly events in New York for Chiefs of Staff. Yo
 u can learn more about my A Chief of Staff New York events here.\n\nAbout 
 Colliers:\n\nSheena and Jen from Colliers work alongside tech companies to
  help make strategic decisions about office\, lab/R&D\, and/or warehouse/d
 istribution space—whether that’s in New York\, San Francisco\, or acro
 ss the globe. We understand that real estate isn’t just about space—i
 t’s about supporting your team\, your culture\, and your mission. From e
 arly-stage startups to managing portfolios for global organizations\, we
 ’ve had the privilege of working with many companies and are always happ
 y to be a resource—whether you’re actively looking for space\, develop
 ing a budget\, exploring options or just have a question!\n\nFeel free to 
 reach out to any one of them\, they would love to connect.\n\nSheena Gohil
 \, New York\n\nJen Flores\, New York\n\n​HEADS UP\n\nBy registering for 
 this event\, you will be added to David's A Chief of Staff Substack newsle
 tter\, so you can keep learning!\n\nCalendar: Personal\n\nHosts: David Neb
 inski\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/re8dg7wa
URL:https://luma.com/re8dg7wa
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-TD3IVnikGvJwagh@luma.com
DTSTAMP:20260706T020844Z
DTSTART:20260716T223000Z
DTEND:20260717T003000Z
SUMMARY:Critical Thinking Club - Is therapy making us more resilient\, or m
 ore reactive?
LOCATION:Work Heights\, Brooklyn\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nNew Yorkers argue a lot. Disagreement has the p
 ower to bring us closer together\, but most of us never learned how. Somew
 here along the way\, speed replaced clarity\, and certainty replaced curio
 sity. The result: we're more polarized\, and less understanding.\n\nCritic
 al Thinking Club aims to reverse that trend by providing space for busy Ne
 w Yorkers who want to think more clearly and communicate more thoughtfully
 . The goal isn’t to "win" an argument\, it’s to improve how we listen\
 , disagree\, and express our opinions without distancing each other.\n\nOu
 r next theme is\, Is therapy making us more resilient\, or more reactive?\
 n\nWe’ll use this topic to practice critical thinking skills like…\n\n
 Articulating views you disagree with\n\nSeparating personal experience fro
 m broader evidence\n\nNoticing hidden assumptions\, in yourself and others
 \n\nRevising your position without compromising your values or credibility
 \n\nWhat to expect\n\n2 comedians debate and a philosophy professor modera
 tes\n\nSmall-group conversations with guided prompts\n\nA psychologically 
 safe environment for disagreement\n\nThe evening begins with a moderated d
 iscussion between 2 comedians who take opposite sides. A professor of phil
 osophy moderates and steps in when reasoning breaks down\, or a common fal
 lacy appears. The moderator pauses to explain\, and suggests how reasoning
  could be improved. Mistakes are expected and useful. The goal is for all 
 of us to share the learnings. Then\, everyone practices in small groups.\n
 \nAgenda\n\n6:30  - 7 PM - Arrive\, chat\, find a seat\n\n7 - 7:05 PM - Su
 mmarize what to expect\, introduce the moderator and speakers\n\n7:05 - 7:
 35 PM - Opening statements\, Q&A\, and closing statements\n\n7:35 - 8:05 -
  Small group discussions (4-6 people) to practice sound critical thinking 
 skills with the help of guided prompts\n\n8:05 - 8:10 - Wrap-up\, particip
 ants can share key takeaways from their group discussions\n\n8:10 - 8:45is
 h - Socialize with the speakers and participants\n\n9 - after party Rocka 
 Rolla\n\nSpeakers\n\nWe’re excited to have Greg Nirshberg moderating our
  next discussion. Greg is the Professor of Philosophy at Iona University\,
  an advisor for the university’s interdisciplinary neuroscience program\
 , and he received his Ph.D. in philosophy at the University of Wisconsin-M
 adison in 2023\, https://www.iona.edu/faculty/nirshberg-gregory\n\nOur nex
 t speakers will be standup extraordinaire Natalie Lin @natalielin._\, and 
 Comedy Cellar regular\, Bassam Shawl @bassamshawl.\n\nIf you want to under
 stand others better\, and be better understood\, join us!\n\nCalendar: Cri
 tical Thinking Club\n\nHosts: KEN LITTON\n\nVenue: Work Heights\n\nEvent p
 age: https://luma.com/v14ee2uc
URL:https://luma.com/v14ee2uc
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-9lA5fLImSygmocB@luma.com
DTSTAMP:20260706T020844Z
DTSTART:20260717T213000Z
DTEND:20260718T003000Z
SUMMARY:The Instagram Playbook: What the Algorithm Actually Wants
LOCATION:BrainStation\, New York\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nThe Social Media Collective by Metricool is bac
 k!\n\nThis time\, we're going deep on Instagram.\n\nWe're bringing togethe
 r social media managers\, creators\, and brand strategists in NYC for an e
 vening built around one question: what does Instagram actually look like i
 n 2026?\n\nMetricool's latest Instagram Study is hot off the press\, one o
 f the largest benchmark reports on Instagram performance\, based on data f
 rom millions of posts. We'll present the findings live\, then open the flo
 or to two expert panels with practitioners who are living this every day.\
 n\nHere's what's on the agenda:\n\n📊 Fresh data from Metricool's 2026 I
 nstagram Study: what's working\, what's changed\, and what it means for yo
 ur content and strategy right now.\n\n🎙️ Panel 1: What the Numbers Ac
 tually Say: brand strategists and social media pros breaking down the data
  from the inside.\n\n🎙️ Panel 2: Real Talk: creators and practitioner
 s sharing what's actually working on Instagram in 2026.\n\n💬 Open Q&A: 
 bring your questions\, we're keeping it honest!\n\n💛 Networking: keep t
 he conversation going after the panels.\n\nWhether you're a social media m
 anager\, a content creator\, a freelancer\, or a brand marketer trying to 
 crack Instagram… there's a place for you in the room.\n\nTHE AGENDA\n\n
 📲 Welcome & Instagram Study Presentation: Metricool team\n 🎙️ Pane
 l 1 · What the Numbers Actually Say -> The Instagram Report\n 🎙️ Pan
 el 2 · Real Talk —> What's Working on Instagram Right Now\n 🤝 Networ
 king & Food\n\nSPEAKERS\n\nWe're bringing together a powerhouse lineup of 
 speakers from across the industry.\n\nSome of the confirmed voices joining
  us so far:\n\nSharon Jacob - The Digital Buff\n\nYemisi Olorunwunmi — H
 ead of Community\, Corporate Chocolate Collective\n\nDino Jevric — Brand
  Social Media Manager\, Arlo Hotels\n\nNasimeh Be — Founder of Somartica
 \n\nArita Muhaxheri — B2B Content Creator\n\nMaría del Pilar Casal — 
 VP\, Televisa Univision\n\nAna Cordera - Meta\n\nAnd more :)\n\nSpots are 
 limited\, grab yours before they're gone. 🔒\n\nBrainStation is the glo
 bal leader in digital skills learning and workforce transformation. We emp
 ower businesses and professionals to thrive in the digital age by providin
 g the skills needed to drive value in areas like AI\, data\, design\, mark
 eting\, and product.\n\nFood & Drinks provided!\n\nCalendar: Metricool\n\n
 Hosts: Metricool\, BrainStation\n\nVenue: BrainStation\n\nEvent page: http
 s://luma.com/23en9fye
URL:https://luma.com/23en9fye
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-LlhzMiRMdutkcUe@luma.com
DTSTAMP:20260706T020844Z
DTSTART:20260718T140000Z
DTEND:20260718T200000Z
SUMMARY:🏆 Builders Cup 2026 - A Hackathon by Ramp
LOCATION:New York\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nPresented by Ramp and sponsored by Cursor\, Cod
 ex\, and Chelsea Commons.\n\nThe ball is in your court. Build something th
 at matters.\n\nRamp is hosting Builders Cup - a one-day hackathon in New Y
 ork City where the best builders compete for prizes\, glory\, and a shot a
 t impressing some of the fastest-growing tech companies in the world. Whet
 her you come with a team or work solo\, this is your chance to ship someth
 ing real\, show what you've got\, and go home with bragging rights (and ma
 ybe some cool prizes).\n\nJoin us for a full day of hacking\, mentorship\,
  demos\, and - yes - very good food.\n\n💰 Prizes\n\nWe're awarding acro
 ss four tracks:\n\nAudience Favorite — the crowd decides. Most votes win
 s.\n\nBest Game — built something fun? This one's for you.\n\nSave Time.
  Save Money. — build anything that saves people time and money.\n\nBest 
 Use of Our Sponsors — more details soon.\n\n🗓️ Day of Schedule\n\n1
 0AM — Doors Open - coffee\, networking\, find your people\n\n10:30AM —
  Kickoff remarks from Ramp and our sponsors\n\n11AM — Hacking starts\n\n
 12PM — Lunch\n\n3:00PM — Demos + awards ceremony\n\n🛠️ What to Ex
 pect\n\nCursor + Codex workshops: live zero-to-one workshops so you can hi
 t the ground running - credits included\n\nMentors on-site to help you shi
 p\n\nCareer fair-style demos: you present at your station\, the crowd vote
 s\, top builders get the spotlight\n\nPrizes for winners\n\nFood\, coffee\
 , and good vibes all day\n\n👤 Who Should Join\n\nCS or software enginee
 ring students graduating 2027 or later\n\nAble to attend in-person in New 
 York City (no travel sponsorship at this time)\n\nBuilders of any experien
 ce level — individual hackers and teams of up to 4 welcome\n\nYou don't 
 need an idea yet. You just need to show up ready to build.\n\n📍 Locatio
 n\n\nFlatiron District\, NYC — exact address shared upon RSVP confirmati
 on.\n\nCalendar: Ramp Emerging Talent\n\nHosts: Richard Noguchi\, Cat Choy
 \, angela\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/nrletiv9
