SUMMARY:Soft Speakers: Hands on eTextiles Workshop
LOCATION:Index Greenpoint\, Brooklyn\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nA hands-on exploration of sound and textiles\, 
 where you'll design and create soft speakers by weaving with conductive th
 reads.\n\nSoft Speakers: Hands on eTextiles Workshop is an introduction to
  the world of eTextiles\, where electronics and textiles merge. In this 3-
 hour session\, you’ll design and build your own woven soft speaker using
  conductive thread and magnets. Designed as an introductory workshop\, par
 ticipants will come away with the basics of weaving and the fundamentals o
 f crafting sound-emitting textiles.\n\nThis workshop is perfect for creati
 ves\, technologists\, craftspeople\, and anyone curious about the intersec
 tion of electronics and materials. You’ll leave not only with a working 
 fabric speaker prototype but also with new insights into how textiles can 
 be used as a medium for technology. By the end of the session\, you’ll b
 e equipped with practical skills to experiment further with eTextiles in y
 our own work.\n\nA hand loom and all necessary materials are included in t
 he registration fee.\n\nProgram\n\nWelcome & Introduction: Overview of the
  workshop and materials\n\nTool Demo: Weaving techniques and speaker basic
 s\n\nBrief Lecture on Speaker Theory: How sound works and the role of mate
 rials in speaker design\n\nDiscussion of Relevant Precedents: Exploration 
 of eTextile projects and inspirations\n\nCrafting Time: Design and create 
 your own woven speaker using conductive fabrics and threads\n\nSymphony of
  Speakers: Test and showcase everyone’s finished speakers in a collectiv
 e sound experience\n\nWrap-Up & Next Steps: Final thoughts and ideas for f
 uture experimentation\n\nLearning Outcomes\n\nHow to use a tapestry loom\n
 \nHow to weave double cloth\n\nHow to create a soft speaker\n\nThe basics 
 of speaker engineering\n\nThe basic of eTextiles\n\nResources\n\nTake a lo
 ok at this workshop page.\n\nFacilitators\n\nCraftwork is a multidisciplin
 ary design and art studio exploring the nature of textiles and technology 
 through installations\, storytelling\, and material-based research. Craftw
 ork co-founders\, Nicole Yi Messier and Victoria Manganiello will be teach
 ing this workshop.\n\nRefunds\n\nWe get that things come up\, but we rely 
 on headcounts in our programs to survive as a business. If you request a r
 efund...\n\nMore than 4 weeks before workshop begins → 100% refund\nMore
  than 2 weeks before workshop begins → 50% refund\nFewer than 2 weeks be
 fore workshop begins → No refund\n\nThanks for understanding and for sup
 porting our ability to provide cool offerings through your purchase.\n\nMe
 dia Release Clause\n\nBy attending this event\, you consent to being photo
 graphed\, filmed\, or recorded\, and grant Index Space permission to use t
 his content for promotional or informational purposes.\n\nCalendar: Index 
 Greenpoint\n\nHosts: Craftwork\n\nVenue: Index Greenpoint\n\nEvent page: h
 ttps://luma.com/index-97rf
URL:https://luma.com/index-97rf
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-HEW4Hhsu8b4IgyP@luma.com
DTSTAMP:20260706T020844Z
DTSTART:20260719T180000Z
DTEND:20260719T200000Z
SUMMARY:Club Rest Stop: Social Rest
LOCATION:Great Hill\, New York\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nClub Rest Stop × Centr: Social Rest\n\nThe tim
 e to rest is now. Join us July 19th — same time\, same place.\n\nA colla
 boration between Club Rest Stop and Centr.\n\nDear Resties\,\n\nOur first 
 meeting was such a hit that we're coming back next month! As you know\, Cl
 ub Rest Stop is all about learning and practicing the seven types of rest.
  Last time\, we explored the rest types and practiced physical rest togeth
 er. This month\, we're turning to social rest — learning how to gauge ou
 r social batteries\, set boundaries around social engagement\, and\, of co
 urse\, rest together.\n\n🌟 In collaboration with Centr\n\nThis month\, 
 we've teamed up with Centr to bring social rest to life. Centr\, founded b
 y Mahika Hari\, is a free app that helps you be a better villager by maint
 aining and deepening the relationships you already have: remembering the p
 ersonal details that matter\, reconnecting more intentionally\, and unders
 tanding your own social battery.\n\nCentr's work lives right at the inters
 ection of social connection\, community\, and wellness\, exactly what soci
 al rest is about. Mahika will co-facilitate with a short talk on the basic
 s\, followed by activities built for practicing different forms of social 
 rest in groups.\n\n🧺 What to expect\n\nRest kits (while supplies last!)
 \n\nA brief\, friendly talk on social rest\n\nA game station for easy\, lo
 w-key connection\n\nA book reading station to slow down\n\nA quiet zone fo
 r resting on your own terms\n\nAnd more!\n\n📍 The details\n\n🗓️ Su
 nday\, July 19 · ⏰ 2–4 PM (programming begins at 2:30 with the social
 -rest presentation\, followed by rest activities and quiet time) · 📍 T
 he Great Hill\, Central Park\, NYC\n\nGetting there: Take the B/C uptown t
 o 103rd St — the exit is directly across from a Central Park entrance. I
 t's a ~5-minute walk (use Google Maps) to the Great Hill\, located right a
 cross from the bathrooms (if you're facing the bathrooms\, the Great Hill 
 is on your right). You'll find us set up on a rainbow blanket. Alternative
 ly\, enter at 106th and follow the signs for "Great Hill."\n\n🎒 What to
  bring\n\nMostly\, just yourself. If you'd like\, feel free to bring somet
 hing that can be shared: craft materials\, cards\, snacks\, baked goods\, 
 etc. It's never required\, but it's a lovely way to break the ice with you
 r fellow Resties.\n\n💌 A few extras\n\nThe community we're building is 
 so special\, and I can't wait to rest with you again.\n\nNew here? Everyth
 ing you need is in your welcome packet\, and we post updates on our TikTok
 .\n\nCurious about Centr? Sign up for early access to the beta and join th
 e waitlist at centrtheapp.com — follow along on TikTok and Instagram\, a
 nd/or follow the Centr Luma page.\n\nMahika is also offering Resties a dis
 counted rate to her Wellness Wednesday community event on sleep health —
  use code RESTIES and join us in learning about how to actually combat bur
 nout and fix your energy levels while enjoying dinner bites\, drinks\, goo
 dy bags\, and making your own embroidered sleep mask!\n\nQuestions? Reach 
 us anytime at cthpress@gmail.com.\n\nIt's time to take a break. See you so
 on. 🤍\n\nCalendar: Centr The App\n\nHosts: Mahika Hari\, Maaliyah P.\n\
 nVenue: Great Hill\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/jdp2y72m
URL:https://luma.com/jdp2y72m
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
