SUMMARY:The Shortlist: July Founder Showcase
LOCATION:New York\, New York
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nThe Shortlist NYC – July Founder Showcase (#6
 )\n\nThe Shortlist is back for our monthly Founder Showcase and the room k
 eeps getting better.\n\nThis is a monthly curated\, application-only eveni
 ng connecting early-stage founders with exceptional operators across New Y
 ork. No panels. No pitches to VCs. Just six founders building breakout com
 panies\, a room full of people who've built things themselves\, and the ki
 nd of candid conversation you don't get at most events.\n\nEach founder wi
 ll share what they're building\, why it matters\, and the specific roles t
 hey're actively hiring for right now — followed by a mixer.\n\nWhat to e
 xpect: Founders presenting at the seed through Series B stage. Operators\,
  builders\, and executives who've seen what good looks like. An intentiona
 lly small room designed for real connection.\n\nWho this is for: Exception
 al operators — whether you're actively exploring your next role\, casual
 ly curious\, or simply want to stay close to what's being built in NYC rig
 ht now.\n\nFounders will be announced in the days leading up to the event.
  👀\n\nAttendance is intentionally limited. Apply to be considered.\n\n.
 ..\n\nMore information on The Shortlist can be found here.\n\nFounded by A
 ndrew Yeung & Ivor Straford.\n\nCalendar: The Shortlist NY\n\nHosts: Sanga
 vi Suresh\, Andrew Yeung\, Betaworks\, Ivor Stratford\n\nEvent page: https
 ://luma.com/shortlistjuly
URL:https://luma.com/shortlistjuly
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
