SUMMARY:Cafe Compute: Gemma in NYC
LOCATION:New York\, New York
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\n"Why are there no coffeeshops open late? But wh
 at if I want to co-work at night?!?" - everyone on Twitter\n\nCerebras and
  Google DeepMind are excited to present Cafe Compute in NYC at Datadog HQ.
 \n\nEnjoy the vibes of a pop-up coffeeshop with a barista bar ☕️\, coz
 y snacks and couches 🛋️\, and more.\n\nCerebras is the world’s fast
 est AI inference\, up to 15x faster than leading GPUs. Cerebras Inference 
 is powered by our Wafer-Scale Engine (WSE-3) - the world's largest AI chip
 . Experience the speed for yourself with OpenAI Codex-Spark\, powered on C
 erebras\, or one of the open source models like GLM 4.7. Get free compute 
 at cerebras.ai.\n\nGemma 4 by Google DeepMind delivers multi-modal frontie
 r-level intelligence across five model sizes\, from ultra-lightweight edge
  models that run offline on your phone to a powerhouse 31B parameter dense
  model that rivals server-grade performance on a laptop.\n\nDatadog is a c
 loud-based observability and security platform. It monitors the health of 
 entire technology stacks. Engineering teams use it to track performance me
 trics\, centralize logs\, and instantly troubleshoot errors across their s
 ystems.\n\nCalendar: Cerebras\n\nHosts: Diyi Zhu\, Cerebras\, Datadog\, Sa
 rah Chieng\, Thor Schaeff\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/cafecomputenyc
URL:https://luma.com/cafecomputenyc
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
