SUMMARY:Bushwick Maker’s Market (Part 7)
LOCATION:114 Forrest St\, Brooklyn\, NY
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nBrowse locally made goods from our community of
  artists and makers - jewelry\, art\, prints\, crochet/knit\, baked treats
 \, tarot readings\, tooth gems\, collages\, and more.  Everything is handm
 ade and a portion of the proceeds go to a mutual aid fund in Lebanon.  Fin
 d a unique gift\, sip something refreshing\, and enjoy the easygoing energ
 y of summer with our creative community. ✨☀️\n\n10-30% of proceeds w
 ill go to Sanad\, a mutual aid fund in Lebanon. Sanad Campaign is dedicate
 d to helping displaced families from South Lebanon\, the Beqaa\, and Baalb
 ek who were forced to leave their homes.\n\nTheir mission is to provide es
 sential support\, secure basic needs\, and help ease the suffering of fami
 lies during these difficult times.\n\nhttps://fundahope.com/en/campaigns/s
 anad-campaign-to-support-displaced-families\n\nCalendar: Personal\n\nHosts
