SUMMARY:The 2026 BKLYN MILE Presented by HOKA
LOCATION:Marsha P. Johnson State Park\, Kings County\, New York
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nThe BKLYN MILE\, presented by HOKA will take pl
 ace on Sunday August 2\, 2026 \n\nThe mile is an iconic distance. Unique i
 n its ability to stoke the fire of the most competitive runner\, but also 
 in its wide appeal to those of all abilities and experience levels.\n\nPar
 ticipants in Brooklyn’s iconic road mile run along Kent Avenue through t
 he heart of Williamsburg. The course is fun\, fast and exhilarating. Perso
 nal bests abound for experienced runners\, and a unique opportunity for be
 ginners and/or back-of-the-packers to experience a unique trip along Willi
 amsburg’s main artery.\n\nREGISTRATION TO OPEN AT NOON ON FRIDAY\, JUNE 
 12\, 2026\n\nUpdates are coming. Stay ready.\n\nCalendar: NYC Running Even
 ts Calendar\n\nHosts: Brooklyn Running Co.\n\nVenue: Marsha P. Johnson Sta
 te Park\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/b8mc6adj
